						               													<description>The Colourable Words Game is a word based competitive family game of 2-4 players played over two phases. In the first phase, players try to score letters with the help of a D6 or D4 on a circular board. Each letter provides points as mentioned on the letter. The letters are divided in 6 colours and the phase enters its last round once a player manages to get letters in each colour. In the second phase players try to create a maximum of three words out of the letters they have scored, with each word providing points. Six letter words score bonus points. The second phase is completed once at least one player finishes putting down all three words. The player with the highest total points over two phases wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
